  "text": "Kupffer cells were isolated from NPCs pooled from the animals in each experimental group and cultured (5 x 10 4 cells/well) in wells of half-area, 96-well plates with 5 mg/mL of LPS (Escherichia coli 0114:B4, Sigma Aldrich, St. Louis, MO) and 100 mL of culture medium as previously described [CITATION_1] . Two days later, culture supernatants were collected and stored at -80uC until analysis. NO . concentrations in the supernatants were estimated using the Griess reagent and the protocol provided by Sigma-Aldrich, St. Louis, MO. Keratinocyte-derived chemokine (KC), MIP-2 and TNF-a concentrations in the supernatants were determined using a MILLIPLEX H MAP kit obtained from Millipore (Billerica, MA) or individual ELISA kits purchased from Peprotech (Rocky Hill, NJ).",
